Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into thin 1cm slices, then chop into
1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over
the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt and @pepper, then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%milliliter},
@sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing.

> See pantry for both amounts.

Season with salt and pepper, mix well, then set your dressing aside.

In a small bowl, combine the @mayonnaise{64%grams} and
@harissa paste{50%grams}.

> Add less if you'd prefer things milder.

Cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks. Grate the @carrot{1}.

Bake the falafels
When the fries have 5-8 mins left, place the @Ready to Eat Falafels{171%grams}
onto another large baking tray. Bake them on the middle shelf of your oven for
the remaining time until golden brown, ~{5-8%minutes}.

A couple of mins before everything's ready, pop the @Plain Taco Tortillas{4}
(2 per person) into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the tomato chunks, grated carrot and @baby leaf mix{20%grams} to the bowl of
dressing and toss together.

> TIP: Don't do this too early or the leaves will go soggy.

Serve
When ready, transfer the tortillas to your plates. Add some salad to each one,
then top with the falafels. Drizzle over some of the harissa mayo, then fold over
both sides of the wraps. Serve your wraps with the spiced fries, any remaining
salad and the remaining harissa mayo alongside. Enjoy!